&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="linenos linenodiv"&gt;&lt;a href="https://dg-pb.github.io/posts/pythons-try-finally/#rest_code_f6a60ab65a1d486c8a2b86c771b02eff-36"&gt;&lt;code data-line-number="36"&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class="code"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;a id="rest_code_f6a60ab65a1d486c8a2b86c771b02eff-36" name="rest_code_f6a60ab65a1d486c8a2b86c771b02eff-36"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;             &lt;span class="k"&gt;break&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;So does it need to be deprecated? Or is even issuing a warning needed?
I would vote for not. Why?
1. Most of languages that faced this issue handled it with linters.
2. Design, although has not been frequently used, is elegant and logical.
3. Faulty usage can be handled by stronger emphasis and education.
4. It is possible that with more education and time it will be picked up and used more often. In the right way.&lt;/p&gt;</description><category>python</category><guid>https://dg-pb.github.io/posts/pythons-try-finally/</guid><pubDate>Sun, 05 Oct 2025 08:10:56 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Feature Test</title><link>https://dg-pb.github.io/posts/feature-test/</link><dc:creator>dg-pb</dc:creator><description>&lt;p&gt;Write your post here.&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid>https://dg-pb.github.io/posts/feature-test/</guid><pubDate>Sun, 05 Oct 2025 07:04:40 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Welcome to Nikola</title><link>https://dg-pb.github.io/posts/welcome-to-nikola/</link><dc:creator>Roberto Alsina</dc:creator><description>&lt;figure&gt;
